"><figure class="media-object-image img-header"><div class="image-container responsive-media"><img width="860" height="573" src="https://images.wsj.net/im-825857?width=860&amp;height=573" alt="" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div><figcaption class="imageCaption"><p class="imageCaptionContent"> President Biden at Andrews Air Force Base, Md., July 28.</p><p class="imageCredit"> Photo: Susan Walsh/Associated Press</p></figcaption></figure></div><p> Owen Daniel&#39;s <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/joe-biden-jimmy-carter-president-kim-strassel-9274606f?mod=article_inline" target="_blank" class="icon none">letter</a> (July 22) praises President Biden. “He steered us out of Covid” (using vaccines developed by President Trump&#39;s Operation Warp Speed). He got us “out of Afghanistan” (by surrendering to the Taliban). “He has assisted Ukraine” (by providing enough arms for Ukraine not to lose but not enough for it to win). “He has mitigated the southern border situation” (by opening the border). “He crafted” an infrastructure bill (that will stoke inflation for years to come). “The US economy is booming” (growing 1% to 2%). “He has shown loyalty . 。 。 for his party without insulting” the other (see: MAGA Republicans and Jim Crow 2.0). Is this what he means by “quiet effectiveness”?</p><p> <strong>George Thomas</strong></p><p> <em>Warren, NJ</em></p></section></div></main></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Fri, 28 Jul 2023 21:13:00 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://www.wsj.com/articles/president-biden-record-covid-afghanistan-ukraine-economy-1e4fdd51</guid><link/> https://www.wsj.com/articles/president-biden-record-covid-afghanistan-ukraine-economy-1e4fdd51<category> biden</category><category> Political/General News</category><category> International Relations</category><category> Health</category><category> Immunizations</category><category> Politics/International Relations</category><category> Medical Treatments/Procedures</category><category> Content 